Add order cancel + test-delete to fulfillment studio

Two new RPCs plus a collapsed danger zone in the order detail pane —
one production-safe, one for pre-launch testing.

Migration additions to 20260424_order_fulfillment.sql:
- cancel_order(order_id, reason) — voids every GTIN on the order
  (never reissued, per GS1), marks order cancelled, preserves audit
  trail. Does not refund the Stripe charge — that stays a manual step
  in the Stripe dashboard.
- delete_order_for_test(order_id) — destructive wipe. Returns GTINs
  to pool as available, deletes product records + audit entries +
  order row. Blocked behind a type-the-prefix confirm in the UI.
  Never call in production once real labels are printed.

Fulfillment Studio UI:
- Engine wrappers: cancelOrder, deleteOrderForTest
- Detail pane gets a collapsed "Danger zone" <details> at the bottom
  (muted red border, hidden until expanded) with two rows — Cancel
  and Delete — each with descriptive copy and a dedicated confirm
  prompt. Delete requires typing the 8-char order id prefix.
- Adds fs-btn--danger and fs-btn--danger-strong variants plus the
  danger zone styling.
